g girl group [[I.O.I]]. Following the dissolution of I.O.I in 2017, Chungha debuted as a solo artist with the [[extended play]] ''[[Hands on Me (EP)|Hands on Me]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nChungha was born as Kim Chan-mi ({{korean|\uae40\ucc2c\ubbf8|labels=no}}) on February 9, 1996, in [[Seoul]], South Korea. Under her English name Annie Kim,<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9R7Uydthkjw&t=46m55s|title=Shooting Live video \u2013 I.O.I appeared to JTBC.|medium=Online video|language=ko|minutes=46|location=South Korea|publisher=[[JTBC|JTBC Entertainment]]|via=[[YouTube]]|date=April 28, 2016|accessdate=August 1, 2019}}</ref> she lived in [[Dallas]], [[Texas]], for eight years before returning to South Korea to become a singer. As a result, she is able to speak both English and Korean.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jang |first1=Yong-hoon |title=\ud32c\ub4e4 \uae5c\uc9dd \ub180\ub77c\uac8c \ub9cc\ub4e0 I.O.I \uae40\uccad\ud558 '\uc601\uc5b4\ud68c\ud654' \uc2e4\ub825 (\uc601\uc0c1) |url=https://www.insight.co.kr/newsRead.php?ArtNo=70796 |website=Insight Korea |accessdate=December 13, 2018 |language=Korean |date=August 5, 2016}}</ref> She graduated from [[Sejong University]], majoring in dance.<ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=\"\ubb34\uc6a9\uacfc 14\ud559\ubc88\" \uae40\uccad\ud558, \ub300\ud559\uc0dd \ubaa8\ub378\ub85c \ucee4\ubc84 \uc7a5\uc2dd[\ud654\ubcf4]|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/076/0003092465|website=Naver|publisher=|accessdate=August 11, 2019|date=May 15, 2017|language=Korean}}</ref> She auditioned for [[YG Entertainment]] and was a [[JYP Entertainment]] trainee prior to joining her current agency [[MNH Entertainment]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Da-som|title=\ud2b8\uc640\uc774\uc2a4 \"'\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4101' \uae40\uccad\ud558 \uc751\uc6d0, \uacfc\uac70 JYP \uc5f0\uc2b5\uc0dd\"(\ud30c\uc6cc\ud0c0\uc784)|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201604271244146610|website=Newsen|publisher=Newsen|accessdate=May 1, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Omega |first1=Jan |title=I.O.I. Finale: Ideal Of Idol Releases Final Track Written By Woozi Of Seventeen Titled 'Downpour' Before Separating [Video] |url=https://www.inquisitr.com/3898597/ioi-finale-ideal-of-idol-releases-final-track-written-by-woozi-of-seventeen-titled-downpour-before-separating-video/ |website=[[Inquisitr]] |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |date=January 19, 2017}}</ref> Kim trained for three years before debuting, and had been dancing for 6\u20137 years. She revealed that she almost quit attending dance classes at some point due to financial issues.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lim|first1=Jasmine|title=K-pop singer Chungha on going from girl group to solo artist|url=https://www.tnp.sg/entertainment/music/k-pop-singer-chungha-going-girl-group-solo-artist|website=The Newpaper|accessdate=August 11, 2019|date=April 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2016\u20132017: ''Produce 101'', I.O.I, and solo debut with ''Hands on Me''===\n{{Main|Produce 101 (season 1)|I.O.I}}\nFrom January 22 to April 1, Kim represented [[MNH Entertainment]] on reality girl group survival show ''[[Produce 101 (season 1)|Produce 101]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Choi |first1=Seong-rok |title=\ub3cc\uc544\uc628 \uccad\ud558... \uadf8\ub140 \uc18c\uc18d\uc0ac \uc774\ub984 \uc55e\uc5d0 'god'\uac00 \ubd99\uc740 \uc774\uc720 |url=http://star.ohmynews.com/NWS_Web/OhmyStar/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0002455715 |website=Oh My News |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=July 20, 2018}}</ref> She finished in fourth place and debuted on May 4, with the project girl group [[I.O.I]] with the mini-album ''[[Chrysalis (EP)|Chrysalis]]''.<ref name=\"4th\">References:\n* {{cite web |title=10 K-Pop Artists to Watch in 2018 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/10-k-pop-artists-to-watch-in-2018-630096/chungha-630165/ |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |date=April 28, 2018 }}\n* {{cite news|title=I.O.I Debuts and Releases \u2032Dream Girls\u2032 MV|author=Jeon Su Mi|url=http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/105102/ioi-debuts-dream-girls-mv|publisher=mwave.interest.me|accessdate=June 2, 2017|date=May 4, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728174714/http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/105102/ioi-debuts-dream-girls-mv|archive-date=July 28, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On June 10, [[YMC Entertainment]] revealed Chungha as one of the seven members of the group's unit group, slated to promote their second single, \"[[Whatta Man (I.O.I song)|Whatta Man]]\", during the summer of 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Park|first1=Hyun-min|script-title=ko:\uc544\uc774\uc624\uc544\uc774, \uccab \uc720\ub2db \ud655\uc815\u2026'\uc804\uc18c\ubbf8\ubd80\ud130 \uae40\uc18c\ud61c'[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5]|url=http://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=109&aid=0003336048|website=Naver|publisher=OSEN|accessdate=June 11, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref> It was revealed that three teams were contacted to make the choreography for the single, but hers was chosen because it was deemed to be the highest quality.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Ye-na|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] '\uc5ed\uc2dc \ucda4\uafbc'\u2026I.O.I \uccad\ud558, \uc720\ub2db \ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1 \uc548\ubb34 \uc9f0\ub2e4|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000895782|website=Naver|publisher=TV Report|accessdate=August 22, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref> The single was a commercial success peaking at number 2 on the [[Gaon Digital Chart]] and on the [[Gaon Album Chart]], for its digital (downloads and streaming) and physical sales respectively.<ref>References:\n* {{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=33&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=August 18, 2016}}\n* {{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=S1020&targetTime=33&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=August 18, 2016}}\n* {{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=S1040&targetTime=33&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=August 18, 2016}}</ref>[[File:20160429 \uae40\uccad\ud558 \uc544\uc774\uc624\uc544\uc774 \ub86f\ub370\uc6d4\ub4dc \uccad\ucd98 \ud398\uc2a4\ud2f0\ubc8c.jpg|thumb|upright|Chungha performing as a member of [[I.O.I]] during the Lotte World Youth Festival in 2016.|alt=Chungha on a stage facing left, she is doing a sideways peace sign around her right eye|left]]On June 30, it was revealed that Chungha would be having a cameo appearance on Korean drama, ''[[Entourage (South Korean TV series)|Entourage]],'' along with groupmate [[Lim Na-young]].<ref>{{cite web|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc774\uc131\ubbfc, '\uc548\ud22c\ub77c\uc9c0' \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \uce74\uba54\uc624 \ud569\ub958..\uc870\uc9c4\uc6c5\uacfc \ud2b9\uae09 \uc758\ub9ac|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0002992135|work=Sports Chosun|access-date=August 19, 2018|last=Cho|first= Ji Young|date=September 26, 2016}}</ref> On July 24, she was revealed to be a new cast member on dance survival show, ''[[Hit The Stage]]''.<ref name=\"6th\">{{cite web |title='\ud79b\ub354\uc2a4\ud14c\uc774\uc9c0' \uc7a5\ud604\uc2b9X\uc2a4\ud14c\ud30c\ub2c8, 2\uc5f0\uc2b9 \ud589\uc9c4\u2026\ucd5c\uc885\uc6b0\uc2b9\ud560\uae4c[\uc885\ud569] |url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/news.htm?id=201608120100113120008311&ServiceDate=20160811 |website=[[Naver]] |publisher=Sports News |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=August 11, 2016}}</ref> On August 17, it was announced that Chungha would be collaborating with groupmates [[Choi Yoo-jung (singer)|Choi Yoo-jung]], [[Jeon So-mi]], and [[Dia (band)|DIA]]'s [[Ki Hui-hyeon]] for the digital single, ''\"''[[Flower, Wind and You]]''\"'', which was produced by Boi B.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201608180919031591625_1|title=MBK \uce21 \"\uae30\ud76c\ud604 \uc804\uc18c\ubbf8 \ucd5c\uc720\uc815 \uae40\uccad\ud558, \ucf5c\ub77c\ubcf4 \ub514\uc2f1 \uc900\ube44\uc911\"|first=Ho-yeon|last=Lee|date=August 18, 2016|work=Herald Pop|language=Korean|accessdate=July 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Choi|first1=Hyun-jung|title=\uae30\ud76c\ud604X\uc804\uc18c\ubbf8X\ucd5c\uc720\uc815X\uae40\uccad\ud558 '\uaf43, \ubc14\ub78c \uadf8\ub9ac\uace0 \ub108' \uc7ac\ud0b7 \uacf5\uac1c|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000498600|website=Naver|publisher=Sports DongA|accessdate=July 12, 2019|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=36&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=Flower, Wind and You|date=August 28 \u2013 September 9, 2016|website=Gaon Music Chart|language=ko|access-date=September 8, 2016}}</ref> The music video was released on [[MBK Entertainment]]'s [[YouTube]] channel. On December 21, MNH Entertainment confirmed that she will be debuting as a solo artist in the beginning of 2017 after wrapping up I.O.I's promotions.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hoong |first1=Gook-hwa |title=FORCE IS FEMALE: \uccad\ud558\uc640\uc758 \uc778\ud130\ubdf0 |url=http://www.vogue.co.kr/2018/10/04/167483/ |website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] Korea |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=October 4, 2018}}</ref> On December 23, Chungha collaborated with [[Heo Jung-eun]] and [[HALO (South Korean group)|HALO]]'s Ooon for the holiday carol, \"Snow in This Year\", that was featured on the Korean drama, ''[[My Fair Lady (2016 TV series)|My Fair Lady]]''.<ref name=\"snow\">{{cite web |title=\uc624 \ub9c8\uc774 \uae08\ube44 OST |url=https://www.melon.com/album/detail.htm?albumId=10031685 |website=[[Melon (online music service)|Melon]] |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=January 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn January 10, 2017, Chungha was selected to be a host for [[Educational Broadcasting System|EBS]]' ''Ah! Sunday \u2013 A Running Miracle''. Chungha would show the public how to improve their physical fitness via jogging and would take a team of challengers under her wing for the show.<ref name =\"5th\">{{cite web |last1=Kim |first1=Ang-soo |title=I.O.I \uae40\uccad\ud558, EBS '\uc544! \uc77c\uc694\uc77c-\uae30\uc801\uc758 \ub2ec\ub9ac\uae30' MC \ubc1c\ud0c1 |url=https://news.nate.com/view/20170110n29233?mid=e0600 |website=[[Nate (web portal)|Nate]] |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=January 10, 2017}}</ref> On April 21, she released her pre-debut single titled \"[[Week (Chungha song)|Week]]\", on the official M&H Entertainment YouTube account,<ref>{{cite web|title=I.O.I \uae40\uccad\ud558, EBS '\uc544! \uc77c\uc694\uc77c-\uae30\uc801\uc758 \ub2ec\ub9ac\uae30' MC \ubc1c\ud0c1|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=111&aid=0000475733&lfrom=twitter|website=Naver|accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref> followed on June 7 by her debut EP, entitled ''[[Hands on Me (EP)|Hands on Me]]'', with the lead track \"[[Why Don't You Know]]\".<ref>{{cite news|date=June 7, 2017|accessdate=June 7, 2017|publisher=[[Yonhap|Yonhap News Agency]]|script-title=ko:[\uc778\ud130\ubdf0] \uae40\uccad\ud558 \"\ub450\ub824\uc6c0\uc774 \ubc18\u2026\ub2e4\uc591\ud55c \uc0c9\uac10 \ub0b4\ub294 \uac00\uc218 \ub420 \uac83\"|url=http://www.yonhapnews.co.kr/bulletin/2017/06/07/0200000000AKR20170607067400704.HTML|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language=ko|date=June 7, 2017|accessdate=June 7, 2017|publisher=[[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS News]]|title=I.O.I \uccab \uc194\ub85c, \uccad\ud558 'Why Dont You Know'|url=http://d.kbs.co.kr/news/view.do?ncd=3494010}}</ref> Chungha subsequently featured in [[Kim Samuel|Samuel Kim]]'s solo debut album entitled ''Sixteen'' with the track \"With U\", and in [[Babylon (singer)|Babylon]]'s single, \"La La La\".<ref>{{cite web|title=\ubca0\uc774\ube4c\ub860, 31\uc77c \uc2e0\uace1 'LaLaLa' \ubc1c\ud45c..\uccad\ud558 \ud53c\ucc98\ub9c1|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003604196|website=Naver|accessdate=September 1, 2017|language=kr}}</ref><ref name=\"Samuel\">{{cite web |title=[V\ub77c\uc774\ube0c \uc885\ud569] '\ub370\ubdd4 1\uc8fc\ub144' \uccad\ud558, \uc774\uc81c\ub294 '\ubcc4\ud558\ub791'\uacfc \ud568\uaed8 |url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=311&aid=0000863088 |website=[[Naver]] |publisher=Esports News |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=June 7, 2018}}</ref> From September 3 onwards, she took over [[Kisum]] as a DJ for [[Educational Broadcasting System|EBS]]'s radio program ''Listen'',<ref name=\"radio\">{{cite news|title=\uccad\ud558, EBS \ub77c\ub514\uc624 DJ \ubc1c\ud0c1 \"\uce5c\uad6c\uac19\uc740 \ubc29\uc1a1 \ub9cc\ub4e4 \uac83\"|url=http://news.jtbc.joins.com/html/418/NB11515418.html|date=August 31, 2017|accessdate=November 11, 2017|language=ko}}</ref> and on September 19, it was announced that she would be an MC for FashionN's ''Please Take Care of My Vanity'' alongside [[Super Junior]]'s [[Leeteuk]] and [[Han Chae-young]].<ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558, '\ud654\uc7a5\ub300\ub97c \ubd80\ud0c1\ud5743' MC \ubc1c\ud0c1\u2026\ub370\ubdd4 \uccab \ubdf0\ud2f0\uc1fc(\uacf5\uc2dd)|url=http://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=311&aid=0000776439|website=Naver|accessdate=September 19, 2017|language=kr}}</ref> On November 22, the first episode of her own reality show, ''Chungha's Free Month'', was released on [[YouTube]] and [[Naver]]TV.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\uccad\ud558, \uc624\ub298(8\uc77c) \uc0dd\uc560 \uccab \ub2e8\ub3c5 \ub9ac\uc5bc\ub9ac\ud2f0 '\uccad\ud558\uc758 \ud504\ub9ac\uba3c\uc2a4' \ucd2c\uc601|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003175843|website=Naver|accessdate=November 11, 2017|language=korean}}</ref>\n\n===2018\u20132019: ''Offset'', ''Blooming Blue'', ''Gotta Go'', and ''Flourishing''===\n[[File:180303_\uccad\ud558_03.jpg|alt=Chungha faces left and faces forward, her hands spread out next to her face|Chungha performing during the [[2018 Winter Paralympics torch relay]], on March 3.|thumb|upright]]\nChungha released her second extended play ''[[Offset (EP)|Offset]]'' on January 17, 2018. The EP contains five tracks including the title track \"[[Roller Coaster (Chungha song)|Roller Coaster]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201801181507046259084_2|title=Chungha rides love's 'Roller Coaster' in new single|accessdate=March 16, 2018|date=January 18, 2018|publisher=kpopherald.com}}</ref> On June 26, MNH Entertainment confirmed that she would be having a comeback on July 18 with her third mini-album titled ''[[Blooming Blue (EP)|Blooming Blue]]'', with \"[[Love U (Chungha song)|Love U]]\" serving as the lead single.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=468&aid=0000398383|script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\uccad\ud558, \ub0b4\ub2ec 18\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815\u2026\ucc28\uc138\ub300 \uc5ec\uc131 \uc194\ub85c \uc544\ud2f0\uc2a4\ud2b8\uc758 \uadc0\ud658 |website= Naver |accessdate=June 26, 2018|date=June 26, 2018|language=korean}}</ref> Chungha became the ambassador for the Seoul International Architecture Film Festival in October of the same year.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bae |first1=Hyo-joo |script-title=ko:\uccad\ud558, \uc11c\uc6b8\uad6d\uc81c\uac74\ucd95\uc601\ud654\uc81c \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac \"\uc18c\uc784 \ub2e4\ud560 \uac83\"(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5) |url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201810080913246710 |website=Newsen |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=October 10, 2018}}</ref> It was announced on August 8 that she would join the project group consisting of [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]'s [[Kang Seul-gi|Seulgi]], [[(G)I-dle]]'s [[Jeon So-yeon|Soyeon]] and [[GFriend]]'s [[SinB (singer)|SinB]] called [[SM Station X 0|Station Young]] for [[SM Entertainment]]'s project album ''[[SM Station X 0]]''. They released their single, \"[[Wow Thing]]\" on September 28.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=144&aid=0000566795|title='SM \uc2a4\ud14c\uc774\uc158\uc601\uc758 \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9\uc740 '\uc2ac\uae30 X \uc2e0\ube44 X \uccad\ud558 X \uc18c\uc5f0'?|publisher=SportsKhan|date=August 8, 2018}}</ref> Chungha collaborated with [[Super Junior]]'s [[Yesung]] with the song, \"Whatcha Doin'\", with the music video released on December 16.\n\nOn January 2, 2019, she released her single album, ''[[Gotta Go (Chungha song)|Gotta Go]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=011&aid=0003475417|script-title=ko:\uccad\ud558 '\ubc8c\uc368 12\uc2dc' \ubba4\ube44 \ud2f0\uc800 \uc601\uc0c1 \uacf5\uac1c '\ubabd\ud658\uc801\uc774\uba74\uc11c\ub3c4 \uc2e0\ube44\ub85c\uc6b4 \ubd84\uc704\uae30' \ud32c\ub4e4 \uae30\ub300\uac10\u2191|website= Naver |accessdate=December 29, 2018|date=December 29, 2018|language=korean}}</ref> On January 9, Chungha won her first-ever [[Music programs of South Korea|music program]] trophy on the [[MBC Music]]'s ''[[Show Champion]]''.<ref name=\"1stwin\">{{cite web |script-title=ko:[\uc885\ud569] '\uc1fc\ucc54\ud53c\uc5b8' \uccad\ud558, \ucef4\ubc31 \ub3d9\uc2dc\uc5d0 1\uc704\u2026\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, \ub824\uc6b1 \ub4f1 \u2605 \ucef4\ubc31\ub7ec\uc26c |url=http://www.xportsnews.com/?ac=article_view&entry_id=1063238 |website=www.xportsnews.com |accessdate=January 9, 2019 |language=ko |date=January 9, 2019}}</ref> She was featured in [[VIXX]] member [[Ravi (rapper)|Ravi]]'s new single, \"Live\", which was released on February 18, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=\ube45\uc2a4 \ub77c\ube44 \uc2e0\uace1 'live' \uc624\ub298(18\uc77c) \uacf5\uac1c \u2026 \uccad\ud558 \ud53c\ucc98\ub9c1 \ucc38\uc5ec|url=http://m.m-i.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=496752|website=entertain.naver.com|accessdate=February 18, 2019 |language=ko |date=February 18, 2019}}</ref> Chungha released her fourth EP ''[[Flourishing (EP)|Flourishing]]'' on June 24, 2019, alongside the music video of the lead single, \"[[Snapping (song)|Snapping]]\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Chungha releases first self-composed song on new album 'Flourishing' |url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20190624000775 |website=The Korea Herald |accessdate=June 24, 2019 |language=en |date=June 24, 2019}}</ref> \"Snapping\" was placed first on ''Show Champion'' on July 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title='\uc1fc!\ucc54\ud53c\uc5b8' \uccad\ud558, 1\uc704 \"\ub354\uc6b1 \ub178\ub825\ud558\ub294 \uccad\ud558 \ub420 \uac83\"|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/241/0002932822|website=Naver|accessdate=July 3, 2019 |language=ko|date=July 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title='\uc1fc\ucc54\ud53c\uc5b8' \uccad\ud558, \ucef4\ubc31\ud558\uc790\ub9c8\uc790 'Snapping'\uc73c\ub85c \uccab 1\uc704[\uc885\ud569]|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/112/0003183719|website=Naver|accessdate=July 3, 2019 |language=ko|date=July 3, 2019}}</ref> In August, she joined the soundtrack lineup for the [[TVN (South Korean TV channel)|tvN]] drama ''[[Hotel del Luna]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://m.koreatimes.co.kr/pages/article.asp?newsIdx=273260|first=Lee|last=Han-na|title=Gummy, Paul Kim and Chungha join soundtrack lineup for \"Hotel Del Luna\"|website=The Korea Times|accessdate=August 2, 2019 |language=ko|date=August 2, 2019}}</ref> The track, titled \"At the End\", was released on August 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|first1=|last1=|url=https://www.msn.com/ko-kr/entertainment/music/\uccad\ud558-\uc624\ub298-3\uc77c-\ud638\ud154-\ub378\ub8e8\ub098-ost-\uadf8-\ub05d\uc5d0-\uadf8\ub300-\uacf5\uac1c\ud669\uae08-\ub77c\uc778\uc5c5-\ud569\ub958-\uacf5\uc2dd/ar-AAFfWKh|title=\uccad\ud558, \uc624\ub298(3\uc77c) '\ud638\ud154 \ub378\ub8e8\ub098' OST '\uadf8 \ub05d\uc5d0 \uadf8\ub300' \uacf5\uac1c..\ud669\uae08 \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5 \ud569\ub958 [\uacf5\u