 throughout her major year and can help guide her to even greater heights in the new decade\". The single was also ranked hundredth on ''Billboard's'' \"The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8544710/best-k-pop-songs-2010s-top-100|title=The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s: Staff List|website=Billboard|language=en-us|access-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2020: Continued success and promotion in the United States===\nIn January 2020, Chungha collaborated with [[Paul Kim (musician, born 1988)|Paul Kim]] on the single \"[[Loveship]]\", which was released on January 21, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=\ud3f4\ud0b4X\uccad\ud558, \ub4c0\uc5e3\uace1 'Loveship' \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\uc5ed\ub300\uae09 \uceec\ub798\ubc84\ub808\uc774\uc158|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/416/0000253931|website=Naver|accessdate=January 13, 2020|language=ko|date=January 13, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chungha and Paul Kim announce upcoming collaboration plans|url=https://gotechdaily.com/chungha-and-paul-kim-announce-upcoming-collaboration-plans/|website=Gotech Daily|accessdate=January 13, 2020|language=en|date=January 13, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558X\ud3f4\ud0b4, \ud2b9\uae09 \ud558\ubaa8\ub2c8 'Loveship' \ubca0\uc77c \ubc97\uc5c8\ub2e4\u2025\ud48b\ud48b\u00b7\uc124\ub818 \ub2f4\uc740 '\uad50\ubcf5\uc0f7' [\u2605SHOT!]|url=https://www.msn.com/ko-kr/entertainment/tv/\uccad\ud558x\ud3f4\ud0b4-\ud2b9\uae09-\ud558\ubaa8\ub2c8-loveship-\ubca0\uc77c-\ubc97\uc5c8\ub2e4\u2025\ud48b\ud48b\u00b7\uc124\ub818-\ub2f4\uc740-\uad50\ubcf5\uc0f7-\u2605shot/ar-BBZaFbc|website=Msn|accessdate=January 21, 2020|language=ko|date=January 21, 2020}}</ref> She was part of the soundtrack lineup for the [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] drama ''[[Dr. Romantic 2]]'' with the track \"My Love\", released on February 4, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558, \u2018\ub7ec\ube0c\uc27d\u2019 \uc774\uc5b4 \u2018\ub098\uc758 \uadf8\ub300\u2019\ub85c \uc62c\ud574 \uc5f0\ucd08\ub294 \uac10\uc131\uc801\uc778 \ub9e4\ub825|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/202002040959053623|website=Hankook Ilbo|accessdate=February 4, 2020|language=ko|date=February 4, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558, '\ub0ad\ub9cc\ub2e5\ud130 \uae40\uc0ac\ubd802' OST \ud569\ub958\u2026\uc624\ub298(4\uc77c) '\ub098\uc758 \uadf8\ub300' \uacf5\uac1c|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/amp/202002047626I|website=Hankyung|accessdate=February 4, 2020|language=ko|date=February 4, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558 '\ub0ad\ub9cc\ub2e5\ud130 \uae40\uc0ac\ubd802' OST \uc5ec\ub35e\ubc88\uc9f8 \uc8fc\uc790 '\ub098\uc758 \uadf8\ub300'[\uacf5\uc2dd]|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/241/0003001581|website=Naver|accessdate=February 4, 2020|language=ko|date=February 4, 2020}}</ref> Chungha made her first comeback in 2020 with a new single, \"[[Everybody Has]]\" on February 29 as part of [[MNH Entertainment]]'s ''[[New.wav]]'' project.<ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558, 29\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815\u2026\uc544\ub974\ub9c8\ub51c\ub85c\uc640 \uc190\uc7a1\uc558\ub2e4(\uacf5\uc2dd)|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/609/0000248468|website=Naver|accessdate=February 17, 2020|language=ko|date=February 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558, 29\uc77c \uc0c8 \uc2f1\uae00 \ubc1c\ud45c\u2026'New.wav(\ub274\uc6e8\uc774\ube0c)' \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/241/0003004750|website=Naver|accessdate=February 17, 2020|language=ko|date=February 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558\ud45c \uac10\uc131 \ubc1c\ub77c\ub4dc \u2018\uc194\uc9c1\ud788 \uc9c0\uce5c\ub2e4\u2019 \uc624\ub298 \uacf5\uac1c (ft.MV \uc870\ubcf4\uc544) [\uacf5\uc2dd]|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/382/0000801955|website=Naver|accessdate=February 29, 2020|language=ko|date=February 29, 2020}}</ref> On March 10, MNH Entertainment announced that Chungha had signed with American agency, [[ICM Partners]], for her America and global promotions.<ref>{{cite web|title=K-Pop Star Chung Ha Signs With ICM Partners: Exclusive|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/9330759/k-pop-chung-ha-signs-with-icm-partners|website=Billboard|accessdate=March 10, 2020|language=en|date=March 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=K-pop singer Chungha signs with US talent agency|url=http://m.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200310000757&ACE_SEARCH=1|website=Korea Herald|accessdate=March 10, 2020|language=en|date=March 10, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uccad\ud558, \u7f8e 3\ub300 \uc5d0\uc774\uc804\uc2dc ICM\uacfc \uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \uacc4\uc57d \uccb4\uacb0, \ubbf8\uad6d \uc9c4\ucd9c \ucd08\uc77d\uae30|url=https://m.sedaily.com/NewsViewAmp/1Z058G38ZQ|website=Sedaily|accessdate=March 10, 2020|language=ko|date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Influences==\nChungha has stated singer [[IU (singer)|IU]] is her role model as she admires the way the soloist is able to sing, dance, and perform various other things.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Septiani Adji |first1=Beryl |title=Chungha Ungkap Artis Solo yang Jadi Panutannya Berkarier di Dunia Entertainment, Siapa? |url=https://www.kanal247.com/media/konten/0000024199.html |website=Kanal247 |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Indonesian |date=December 11, 2018}}{{Unreliable source?|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Endorsements and promotions==\nChungha has endorsed various products ranging from electronics to clothing and cosmetics. Her first endorsement was for [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]'s \"Nike x W Korea\", alongside singer [[Amber Liu (singer)|Amber Liu]] and dancer May J Lee in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:#\ub098\uc774\ud0a4\uc6b0\uba3c \ub098\uc774\ud0a4 X \ub354\ube14\uc720 \u2018Women\u2019s Revolution\u2019 1\ud3b8 LIVE|url=http://www.wkorea.com/2017/02/27/\ub098\uc774\ud0a4\uc6b0\uba3c-\ub098\uc774\ud0a4-x-\ub354\ube14\uc720-womens-revolution-1\ud3b8/|website=WKorea |accessdate=August 12, 2019|date=February 27, 2017|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\nChungha's endorsements includes modeling for [[Umbro]],<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:\ucea0\uc2a4\ucf58, \uc544\uc774\uc624\uc544\uc774(I.O.I) \uccad\ud558\u318d\ubaa8\ub378 \uc5d8\ub9ac\uc2a4\uac00 \ud568\uaed8\ud55c \ud654\ubcf4 'FANTASTIC WINTERLAND' \uacf5\uac1c|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/011/0003212273|website=Naver|accessdate=August 12, 2019|date=February 1, 2017|language=Korean}}</ref> women's clothing brand Muzak Ifne,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.apparelnews.co.kr/m/mnews.php?table=internet_news&query=view&uid=77674|title='\ubb34\uc790\ud06c', '\uc774\ud504\ub124' \uc0c8 \ubba4\uc988\ub294 \uac00\uc218 \uccad\ud558|date=August 2, 2019|accessdate=August 12, 2019|language=ko}}</ref> Lens Town's contact lenses,{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}} endorsing [[Lotte Chilsung|Lotte Liquor]]'s 'Chungha',<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\uc62c\ud574 34\uc0b4\ub41c \ub86f\ub370\uc8fc\ub958 '\uccad\ud558'\uac00 \uafb8\uc900\ud788 \uc0ac\ub791 \ubc1b\ub294 5\uac00\uc9c0 \ube44\uacb0|url=https://m.insight.co.kr/amp/news/205197|website=Insight.co|accessdate=August 12, 2019|date=January 18, 2019|last=|first=|language=ko}}</ref> and being the brand model for Guljak Topokki Chicken restaurant.<ref>{{cite web |title=\uccad\ud558, \uac78\uc791\ub5a1\ubcf6\uc774\uce58\ud0a8 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc \ubaa8\ub378\ub85c \ub4f1\uadf9 |url=http://www.seoulwire.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=195709 |website=seoulwire.com |accessdate=August 17, 2019 |language=ko |date=August 13, 2019|first=Myung-cheol|last=Lee}}</ref> She has also endorsed the video games ''Sudden Attack'' and ''Bosslave'', and [[LG Corporation]]'s mobile service U+ 5G.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chungha Turns into a Fighter in New 'Sudden Attack' CF|url=http://www.koogle.tv/media/news/chungha-turns-into-a-fighter-in-new-sudden-attack-cf/|website=Koogle |accessdate=August 12, 2019|date=February 14, 2019|last=Shin|first=Banseok|language=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bbs.ruliweb.com/news/read/125765|title=\ub8fd\ud22c\ucf54\ub9ac\uc544 \uc2e0\uc791 '\ubcf4\uc2a4\ub808\uc774\ube0c' \ud64d\ubcf4\ubaa8\ub378\ub85c \uccad\ud558 \ubc1c\ud0c1|work=Ruli Web|date=August 1, 2019|accessdate=August 12, 2019|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.techholic.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=181538|title=LGU+, \uad6d\ub0b4 \uc774\ud1b5\uc0ac \ub2e8\ub3c5 '\uac24\ub7ed\uc2dcS10 5G' \uac1c\ud1b5 \uc804\uc57c\uc81c|work=Tech Holic|date=April 5, 2019|access-date=August 12, 2019|language=ko}}</ref> In March 2019, [[Clinique]] announced that they had worked with and chosen Chungha as the brand's global ambassador.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:\uc2e0\ub77c\uba74\uc138\uc810, \uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \ubdf0\ud2f0 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc `\ud06c\ub9ac\ub2c8\ud06c`\uc640 \ud31d\uc5c5 \ud589\uc0ac|url=http://m.mk.co.kr/news/company/2019/385620/|website=MK |accessdate=August 12, 2019|date=June 5, 2019|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:\uccad\ud558, 2019 \ud06c\ub9ac\ub2c8\ud06c \uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \uc570\ubc84\uc11c\ub354 \ubc1c\ud0c1|url=http://mnews.jtbc.joins.com/News/Article.aspx?news_id=NB11778859|website=JTBC News|accessdate=August 12, 2019|date=March 6, 2019|language=Korean}}</ref> In May 2019, [[Sprite (drink)|Sprite]] Korea announced her as the new model and face of the brand and their Summer 2019 ''Dive in Sprite'' Campaign alongside actor [[Jang Ki-yong]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mk.co.kr/star/hot-issues/view/2019/05/296089/|title=\uccad\ud558X\uc7a5\uae30\uc6a9, \uc2a4\ud504\ub77c\uc774\ud2b8 \uc0c8 \ubaa8\ub378 \ubc1c\ud0c1...\"\ucfe8\uc139\uc2dc \uc2a4\ud0c0\"|work=Star MK|date=May 7, 2019|access-date=June 7, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Chungha discography}}\n{{See also|List of songs recorded by Chungha}}\n{{For|Chungha's works with [[I.O.I]]|I.O.I discography}}\n\n===Extended plays===\n* ''[[Hands on Me (EP)|Hands on Me]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Offset (EP)|Offset]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[Blooming Blue (EP)|Blooming Blue]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[Flourishing (EP)|Flourishing]]'' (2019)\n\n==Filmography==\n{{For|Chungha's work with [[I.O.I]]|I.O.I#Filmography}}\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Original title\n! Role\n! Network\n! Notes\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Entourage (South Korean TV series)|Entourage]]''\n| \uc548\ud22c\ub77c\uc9c0\n| rowspan=\"4\"|Herself\n| [[TVN (South Korea)|tvN]]\n| Episode 1 with [[Lim Na-young]]||<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kim |first1=Kyeong-bin |title=tvN '\uc548\ud22c\ub77c\uc9c0' \uc544\uc774\uc624\uc544\uc774\ubd80\ud130 \ud558\uc815\uc6b0\uae4c\uc9c0\u2026\uc5ed\ub300\uae09 \uce74\uba54\uc624 10\uc778 |url=https://www.insight.co.kr/newsRead.php?ArtNo=67064 |website=Insight Korea |accessdate=December 14, 2018 |language=Korean |date=June 30, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Idol Drama Operation Team]]''\n| \uc544\uc774\ub3cc \ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 \uacf5\uc791\ub2e8\n| [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]\n| Episode 5, 6\n| <ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title= [\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uae40\uccad\ud558, '\uc544\uc774\ub3cc \ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 \uacf5\uc791\ub2e8' \ud2b9\ubcc4\ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026\uc804\uc18c\ubbf8 \ub9cc\ub09c\ub2e4|url= https://news.nate.com/view/20170410n29554?mid=e0100|website=News Nate|accessdate=January 20, 2020|language=Korean|date=April 10, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2018\n| ''[[YG Future Strategy Office]]''\n| YG\uc804\ub7b5\uc790\ub8cc\ubcf8\ubd80\n| [[Netflix]]\n| Episode 4\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.osen.co.kr/article/G1111003175|title='YG\uc804\uc790' \uc2b9\ub9ac\uac00 \uc774\ub048 YG \uc140\ud504\ub514\uc2a4, B\uae09\uc720\uba38 \ud3ed\ubc1c..\ubc15\ubd04\u00b7\ub0a8\ud0dc\ud604 \ub4f1\uc7a5(\uc885\ud569)[Oh!\uc388 \ub9ac\ubdf0]|website=OSEN|language=ko|access-date=October 5, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Top Management (TV series)|Top Management]]''\n| \ud0d1 \ub9e4\ub2c8\uc9c0\uba3c\ud2b8\n| [[YouTube Premiu